GNOME System Monitor is a GNOME process viewer and system monitor with an
attractive, easy-to-use interface, It has features, such as a tree view for
process dependencies, icons for processes, the ability to hide processes that
you don't want to see, graphical time histories of CPU/memory/swap usage, the
ability to kill/renice processes needing root access, as well as the standard
features that you might expect from a process viewer.
